# MediaForge Icon Guidelines

MediaForge uses custom-generated icons with specific styles. This document outlines the icon generation process and usage guidelines.

## Icon Style

Current MediaForge icon style:
- Modern "M" letter design with gradient color scheme
- Purple-blue color palette
- Rounded/oval style elements
- Clean, professional appearance

## Icon Generation Process

1. Create SVG source design in [tmp/MediaForgeIcon/](mdc:tmp/MediaForgeIcon/)
2. Use CairoSVG Python scripts to generate all required sizes:
   - [convert_m_exact_icon.py](mdc:tmp/MediaForgeIcon/convert_m_exact_icon.py) for generating all Mac app icon sizes
3. PNG outputs are placed in the output directory and then copied to:
   - [MediaForge/Assets.xcassets/AppIcon.appiconset/](mdc:MediaForge/Assets.xcassets/AppIcon.appiconset/)

## Required Icon Sizes

macOS app icons require these specific sizes (both 1x and 2x resolution):
- 16x16
- 32x32
- 64x64
- 128x128
- 256x256
- 512x512
- 1024x1024 (App Store)

## Tips for Icon Updates

1. When updating icons, ensure all sizes are regenerated
2. Update the application bundle icon reference
3. Refresh the system cache with `touch MediaForge.app && killall Dock`
